GENERAL
=======

-- Multiline: use dopart slots instead of inlined code in interface.

-- add onAboutToClose::(# do terminate #) in all demos/tutorials.

- Move all bitmaps to
  ~beta/bitmap/bifrost and
  ~beta/bitmap/mjolner.

- Find all occurrences of "error!" and try if the compiler can handle them.

- Maybe problem with first event in sequence under motif.

- Two refresh events at opening of window under guienv?

- Implement IntegerList (if needed)

- Implement all patterns marked with "(* Not Yet Implemented *)" or that
  calls the pattern UnImplemented.
  Currently this is:
      AbstractGraphicalObject.InteractiveScale
      AbstractGraphicalObject.InteractiveRotate
      PictureShape.GetControls
      Picture.InteractiveCreateShape
      Picture.InteractiveReshape
      Picture.InteractiveCombineShape
      Bitmap.WriteToPBMfile
      GrayMap
      Shape.Insert
      Shape.Delete
      Shape.AppendShape
      Shape.ConnectShape
      Shape.ConnectShapeSmooth
      Line.dashes
      MultiLine.dashes
      PixMap.WriteToPPMfile
      PixMap.ReadFromPPMfile
      Picture.DrawOnPixmap
      TiledSolidColor.writePS (implemented, but hotspot not accounted for)
      RasterPaint.writePS (much like TiledSolidColor.writePS)
      WinNT: 
      	PixMap.ReadFromPBMfile
	TiledSolidColor
      Macintosh:
	The current version of Bifrost is not available for Macintosh.

- In PaintXXXimpl, objects not being drawn by control points should
  remember to scale width, heights (e.g Rect, Ellipse).
  And all objects should handle scaling of line widths.
  Not to mention rotations, but here it gets tricky, because e.g. 
  the X11 primitives for drawing ellipses/rectanles do NOT allow for
  non-axisparallel objects.

- Use ObjectPool for PathHandler
   
- In readpbmfile: Furtherbind binary::<trueobject if RAWBITS.
  However, since whitespace is ignored, it is probably not needed.

- Opgrade the animation package.

- InteractionHandler should look more like eventhandler
  (doubleclick and event names are not the same).

- Not really a bifrost problem, but here I often meet the problem:
  Hardspace in source files confuses BETA-parser 
  (e.g. in macintosh files).
  Compiler should print these as e.g. \017 in lst file.

- 0->PutPixel is not implemented under X11 (i.e. resetting of
  a pixel).

- initCanvas: check that fonts are initialized.

- Maybe there are too many operations on Canvas, now that it 
  inherits from guienv.Canvas? E.g. Map/Unmap.

- Add PredefinedGraphicalObject RoundRect.
  X11 implementation can be done using a Public Domain X11 extension.

- WriteEPS: add parameters "fit", "border", "margin".

- Use the copy operation suggested in the BETA FAQ instead of the 
  current implementation.

- X11 impl: Maybe allocate own collormap, to prevent
  color allocation from failing.
  E.g. demo/colorscale on some servers.

- postscript generation for paints other than SolidColor.
  TiledSolidColor should be easy.

- Paints other than SolidColor are not implemented for WinNT.

- Possibly handle Milimeters properly by changing Canvas.TM

- Possibly rename RasterPaint to PixmapPaint or ImagePaint.

- resize must call UpdateCoordinateSystem

- A PieChart demo would be nice.

- open/close: destroy picture.

- ReadPBM: getFileRep.

- Predefined: Check that enterTM is only a translation (+scale?)

- Optimize getcontrols.

- Implement IntegerList

- All getBounds and FillXXX: Must handle general transformations.

- Palette.Break: breaks current row/column.

- Paletter.NoOfItems: [1]@integer;

- Demo showing that multiple controlpoints a same positions pulls the
  spline more.

- Possibly add Raster.PutPixels (plural!).
   (# positions: ^PointArray;
      p: ^pixel
   enter (positions[], p[])
   do ...
   #);
  Allows for only one color allocation.
  X: Possibly XPutPoints + mask or XDrawPoints.

- Generalize arrow library from Freja to general bifrost lib.

BDRAW
=====

- Se README for generelle fejl/mangler

- Put implementation files into a private directory.

- Jeg har bemærket en underlig opførsel i bdraw:
  Prøv at tegne en ellipse i bdraw;
  Tryk derefter en enkelt gang på et af hjørnerne;
  Og vupti: ellipsen er skrumpet til micro størrelse.
  Jeg har ikke selv gjort noget for at kigge efter hvor fejlen ligger.
  Jeg er derfor ikke helt sikker på om det bare er en fejl i bdraw,
  eller om det er en fejl i Bifrost. 
  /Peter Ahe

- Duplicate: If two objects selected, and Duplicate is performed,
  one of the two new objects will be highlighted wrong.

- Immediate paste puts the new object into position (0,0).

- Cut+Copy: Update clipboard (if visible)

- Update menus when selection changes (enable/disable items)

- Add extensions.pagesize: @rectangle

- Palette med patterns og colors.
  MySolidColor skal være TiledSolidColor.

- Palette med line styles (stipple, arrows)


